item.title: Death Clock
item.dc:creator: @XxKanexX Kane.
item.description:
@XxKanexX wrote:

[quote=“The Un-Named, post:59, topic:80703”][quote author=Hiaburi link=topic=118531.msg1185369#msg1185369 date=1177070729]

idk if neone pointed it out but that site works by assuming any normal person will live to 73 years old, sadists live less or sumthin like that.

No, the site works by taking your details and comparing it to an average lifespan of someone with the same details.

By no means is it random.
[/quote]thats what i ment…basicaly, last i checked it doesnt change if you choose smoking or not smoking, and most of the time it sais ur gunna die when ur 73, at least thats what it used to be like

It’s a little more complex than that, I’m sure drastic BMI’s will affect it, also it may take into consideration if you where born say 1940 that you have the flu from that time or something like that.[/quote]
Roughly it’d just be like

(however old men & woman live for)
manage = 74
womanage = 74

then it’d be like
if (smoker = true) then manage = manage - soandsoyears

with BMI it’d probably just be like
if (BMI >= fatty) then manage = manage - 4;
if (BMI <= anorexic) then manage = manage - 4;

ect.
